The elected member of the House of Representatives for Darazo/Ganjuwa in Bauchi State, Mansur Manu Soro, has reached out to his constituents in the spirit of Ramadan. Soro who was elected on the platform of the APC, said he was elated because the constituents gave him more votes than what the PDP, PRP and NNPP candidates got. He disclosed this during the distribution of 2,000 medium sized bags of rice he donated to party officials, indigents and MMS (Mansur Manu Soro) Campaign Ambassadors. According to him, he garnered 45,867 votes to defeat other candidates in the February 23, election. Soro informed that the gesture was to appreciate the support given to him by his constituents which gave him the opportunity to represent them at the Green Chamber of the National Assembly. Manu-Soro walks to the parliament Allegations against Tradermoni mischievous â€“ APC Reps candidate Bauchi APC House of Reps candidate trains 1000 women on oil milling Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin